# Message Consolidator Deployment Procedure

This document outlines the steps to build and deploy the application to the VPS environment.

## Prerequisites
- Google Cloud SDK (`gcloud`) configured with the target project.
- Access to the target VPS (`chat-analyzer-vps`).
- `.env` file with correct production credentials.

## Deploy to VPS
# Address: https://34.67.133.18.nip.io/
# Service port: 8080

### 1. Build the Binary Locally
Build the Go binary for the target production environment (Linux/AMD64) on your local machine. This is much faster than building on a low-spec VPS.
```bash
# Use CGO_ENABLED=0 for faster, statically linked builds (CGO is no longer needed since sqlite3 was removed)
go mod tidy
CGO_ENABLED=0 GOOS=linux GOARCH=amd64 go build -o message-consolidator-vps .
```

### 2. Transfer Files to GCS
Upload the pre-built binary and other necessary files to Google Cloud Storage.
```bash
# Upload binary and config files to GCS
gcloud storage cp message-consolidator-vps .env docker-compose.yml Dockerfile.runtime gs://message-consolidator-deploy-gemini-enterprise-487906/vps/ --project=gemini-enterprise-487906

# Upload static folder (recursive)
gcloud storage cp -r static gs://message-consolidator-deploy-gemini-enterprise-487906/vps/ --project=gemini-enterprise-487906
```

### 3. Deploy on VPS
Connect to the VPS, download files from GCS, and restart the containers.
```bash
gcloud compute ssh chat-analyzer-vps --zone=us-central1-a --project=gemini-enterprise-487906 --command="
  mkdir -p ~/message-consolidator && 
  cd ~/message-consolidator && 
  gcloud storage cp gs://message-consolidator-deploy-gemini-enterprise-487906/vps/* . && 
  gcloud storage cp -r gs://message-consolidator-deploy-gemini-enterprise-487906/vps/static . &&
  cp Dockerfile.runtime Dockerfile && 
  sudo docker-compose down && 
  sudo docker-compose up -d &&
  sudo docker image prune -f
"
```

### 4. Verify Logs
Check the application logs to ensure successful startup.
```bash
gcloud compute ssh chat-analyzer-vps --zone=us-central1-a --project=gemini-enterprise-487906 --command="sudo docker logs message-consolidator_app_1 --tail 50"
```

## Important Notes
- **Static Assets**: The `static/` directory is volume-mounted (`./static:/app/static`). Updates to files in `static/` on the VPS host will be reflected immediately in the running container. You don't need to rebuild the image if only static assets were changed.
- **Environment Variables**: Always verify the `.env` file on the VPS matches the production requirements, especially the Google OAuth credentials and `APP_BASE_URL`.
